# Centralized styling + logging

## Fonts & typography
- **Typography must be centralized in** `theme/tokens.ts` (use `typography.*` styles).
- **Font families**:
  - **Titles**: Palanquin (see `fonts.title*`)
  - **Body/UI**: Montserrat (see `fonts.body*`)
- Fonts are loaded globally in `app/_layout.tsx`. Do not add ad-hoc font loading elsewhere.
- Avoid hardcoding `fontFamily`/`fontWeight` in screens; prefer `typography` tokens.

## Dynamic Type (accessibility font scaling) — STRICT RULES

### 1. Always use `<AppText>` — never `<Text>` from react-native
`AppText` (`components/AppText.tsx`) handles `allowFontScaling`, `maxFontSizeMultiplier`, and auto-scales `lineHeight` when the user increases their system font size. Using raw `<Text>` bypasses all of this. ESLint enforces this via `no-restricted-imports`.

### 2. Never use `fontWeight` without `fontFamily`
`fontWeight` alone silently falls back to the system font (SF Pro on iOS, Roboto on Android), ignoring the custom Montserrat/Palanquin fonts. Always specify `fontFamily` from `theme/tokens.ts`:

| Desired weight | Use |
|---|---|
| Regular | `fontFamily: fonts.bodyRegular` |
| Medium | `fontFamily: fonts.bodyMedium` |
| SemiBold | `fontFamily: fonts.bodySemi` |
| Bold / 700+ | `fontFamily: fonts.bodyBold` |
| Title Bold | `fontFamily: fonts.titleBold` |
| Title Semi | `fontFamily: fonts.titleSemi` |

Weights 800/900 are not loaded — use `fonts.bodyBold`. Drop `fontWeight` entirely when setting `fontFamily`; the font file encodes the weight.

When overriding a token spread (e.g. `{ ...typography.bodyRegular, … }`), use `fontFamily` not `fontWeight`:
```tsx
// ✗ wrong
{ ...typography.bodyRegular, fontWeight: "600" }

// ✓ correct
{ ...typography.bodyRegular, fontFamily: fonts.bodySemi }
```

### 3. Always pair `fontSize` and `lineHeight` together
`AppText` auto-scales `lineHeight` using `useWindowDimensions().fontScale` capped at `maxFontSizeMultiplier`. If you set `lineHeight` without `fontSize` in the same style object, the ratio will be wrong at large font sizes. Always set both, or use a `typography.*` token which already includes both.

## Layout & tokens
- Prefer `theme/tokens.ts` (`colors`, `spacing`, `radii`, `typography`) + `theme/styles.ts` (`card`, `row`, `layout`) over duplicating raw hex values and magic numbers.
- If a new reusable style pattern appears in 2+ screens, promote it into `theme/styles.ts` or a token.

## NativeWind / Tailwind usage
- NativeWind is available; if using `className`, prefer `font-montserrat` / `font-palanquin` over custom font definitions.
- Keep Tailwind usage consistent with tokens; don’t invent one-off colors/spacings that diverge from `theme/tokens.ts`.

## Logging
- Use the centralized logger: `import { logger } from "@/lib/logger";`
- Prefer tagged logs: `logger.info("screenName", "message", data)`.
- Do not add new `console.log/warn/error` in app code (except inside `lib/logger.ts`).

